  .modal-body

    #application_arrownav_page_1.arrownav_page

      #modal_help_page_1
        .offset28
          %h3 ...how to get around
        .set-1a
          %h4 i) Map
          %p Find and contact other candidates to practise with
        .set-1b
          %h4 ii) Roulette
          %p Practise a case with someone else online now
        .set-1c
          %h4 iii) Help
          %p Instructions on the different elements of the site
        .set-1d
          %h4 iv) Feedback
          %p Tell us about bugs, or suggest new features
        .set-1e
          %h4 v) Notifications
          %p All correspondance from your contacts can be found here. It is also where you can approve case partner requests
        .set-1f
          %h4 vi) Profile Menu
          %ul
            %li
              %b
                Case Index - 
              Review all of your feedback
            %li
              %b
                Progress Analysis -
              See graphical analysis of your feedback
            %li
              %b
                Settings -
              Edit your profile

    #application_arrownav_page_2.arrownav_page
      #modal_help_page_2
        .offset19
          %h3 ...find other candidates to practise with
        .set-2a
          %h4 i) The Map
          %p Find for other candidates who or work near you - click on a marker to see their profile
        .set-2b
          %h4 ii) User panel
          %p Browse for other candidates - click on a candidates list entry to see their profile
          %p Select 'contacts' to see your approved case partners
        .set-2c
          %h4 iii) World Surfer
          %p Use this to jump to places around the world where there are other candidates
        .set-2d
          %h4 iv) User Profile
          %p When two candidates approve each other as case partners, they can send messages and feedback to each other at anytime
          %p When you send a case partner request, sell yourself and explain why they might want to practise with you


    #application_arrownav_page_3.arrownav_page
      #modal_help_page_3
        .offset25
          %h3 ...practise with someone now
        .set-3a
          %h4 i) Connect
          %p Click the 'Join' button to connect to case roulette
          %p You are now visible as 'online' to all other users on the roulette page
          %p Sit back, relax and wait for other users to contact you
        .set-3b
          %h4 ii) Roulette Request
          %p When another user sends you a request, a popup will appear on your screen, showing the other user's status and their Skype address.
          %p Click the 'call me' button, to call them on Skype and start a case, if you wish
          %p Alternatively find candidates in the list, and send them a request yourself
        .set-3c
          %h4 iii) Jump to Skype to start a case
          %p Candidates on the roulette are likely not to be your case partners, so as a security measure, to send them feedback on the case, ask the interviewee for their 'roulette token', a ranomly generated code, at the top of the page.
          %p Enter their code into your roulette window to be taken to a feedback form for them

    #application_arrownav_page_4.arrownav_page
      #modal_help_page_4
        .offset15
          %h3 ...fill out a feedback form for your case partner
        .set-4a
          %p Feedback system carefully designed by a consultant at one of the top 3 firms with many years of interviewing experience
        .set-4b
          %h4 i) Top 3 Recommendations
          %p Enter your Top 3 recommendations, specifying what you thought they need to prioritise in their preparation
        .set-4c
          %h4 ii) Scoring Criteria
          %p The three main criteria Business Analytics, Interperonsal and Structure and their sub-criteria represent the areas on which candidates most often fail
          %p To see more instructions on how to mark these criteria move your mouse over a sub-criteria's name
        .set-4d
          %h4 iii) Move the Sliders
          %p Move sliders to give a user a score between 1-10 for each sub-criteria - you are required to give a score on each.
          %p The sub-scriteria scores are aggregated to an average score for the main criteria
        .set-4e
          %h4 iv) Make Comments
          %p Enter your comments in the text boxes on the right for each criteria

    #application_arrownav_page_5.arrownav_page
      #modal_help_page_5
        .offset25
          %h3 ...review your case feedback
        .set-5a
          %h4 A Library of your cases
          %p Browse and search for cases you've done in the list on the left.
        .set-5b
          %p
            Clicking on a case brings up the record for it,
            %br
              showing graphs of your scores,
              %br
                and the comments made by the interviewer.

    #application_arrownav_page_6.arrownav_page
      #modal_help_page_6
        .offset25
          %h3 ...so this is just a bit of fun
        .set-6b
          %h2 The Progress Chart
          %p Shows your aggregated scores for the three categories over time
        .set-6c
          %h2 Radar Chart
          %p In the bottom left shows your scores for your first and last case, as well as your overall average, against the different scoring criteria - look for things you are consistenly weak at to improve
        .set-6d
          %h2 Comment Aggregator
          %p Use the comment aggregator to browse through comments in the different categories, and recommendations, to remind yourself of what you need to improve.


  .modal-footer
    .pull-left
      #modal_help_checkbox

